To me, &quot;Shiva justice&quot; could be interpreted as &quot;cosmic justice&quot; or  
the immutability of Karma as a natural element of creation--a fancy  
way of saying that it comes right in the end, although we may not be  
able to see it with our limited eyes. Or, as the plants at FIndhorn,  
Scotland, used to say, &quot;Be calm and know that all is very well&quot; (en  
perpetua, as opposed to this very moment, although the eternal is  
reflected in the moment).

Ann



